===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable}} The [[digit]] or [[figure]] 4; an occurrence thereof.
# {{lb|en|countable}} Anything measuring four [[unit]]s, as [[length]].
#: {{ux|en|Do you have any more '''fours'''? I want to make this a little taller.}}
# Four o'clock.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Pigot and Co.'s National Commercial Directory for 1828-9, Comprising a Directory of the Merchants, Bankers, Professional Gentleman [...] in the Counties of Cheshire, Cumberland [...]|passage=Letters to Sheffield are despatched every morning at six, and arrive every afternoon at ten minutes past '''four'''.|year=1828|page=767|pageurl=https://www.google.ca/books/edition/Pigot_and_co_s_national_commercial_direc/hdMHAAAAQAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&pg=PA767|publisher=J. Pigot & Co.|location=London; Manchester|url=https://www.google.ca/books/edition/Pigot_and_co_s_national_commercial_direc/hdMHAAAAQAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=0}}
#* {{RQ:Carlyle Friedrich|chapter=IX|volume=VI|passage=Frederick, I presume, at this late hour of '''four''', may be snatching a morsel of dinner; {{...}}}}
#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Amphibians Came to Conquer: The Story of Admiral Richmond Kelly Turner|passage=The larger ships picked up the low lying atoll on their radar about '''four''' in the morning at distances from 16 to 26 miles.|year=1972|author=George Carroll Dyer|page=657|pageurl=https://www.google.ca/books/edition/The_Amphibians_Came_to_Conquer/6ga4abz2UgMC?hl=en&gbpv=1&pg=PA657|chapter=XVII|volume=2|ol=OL46887398M|publisher=U.S. Marine Corps|location=|edition=|url=https://www.google.ca/books/edition/The_Amphibians_Came_to_Conquer/6ga4abz2UgMC?hl=en&gbpv=0}}
# A person who is four [[year]]s old.
#: {{ux|en|I'll take the threes, '''fours''' and fives and go to the playground.}}
# {{lb|en|cricket|countable}} An [[event]] in which the batsmen run four times between the wickets or, more often, a [[batsman]] hits a ball which bounces on the ground before passing over a [[boundary]], resulting in an award of 4 [[run]]s for the batting team. If the ball does not bounce before passing over the boundary, a [[six]] is awarded instead.
# {{lb|en|basketball|countable}} A [[power forward]].
# {{lb|en|rowing}} Four-man [[sweep]] racing shell, with or without a [[coxswain]].
## The shell itself.
##: {{ux|en|The team bought a new '''four''' last season.}}
## The [[crew]] rowing in a four boat.
##: {{ux|en|Our '''four''' won both races.}}
## {{lb|en|colloquial}} A [[regatta]] event for four boats.
##: {{ux|en|We got third place in the varsity '''four'''.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A four-[[pennyworth]] of spirits.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1887|author=Sir Arthur Conan Doyle|title=A Study in Scarlet|section=IV
|passage=I was a-strollin' down, thinkin' between ourselves how uncommon handy a '''four''' of gin hot would be, when suddenly the glint of a light caught my eye in the window of that same house.}}

